The paper deals with graph deletion problems in the context of data streams, which involves algorithms and data structures for processing large amounts of data in a limited amount of memory. This falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of graph theory and computational complexity, which falls under "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC) and "Graph Theory" (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with adjacency lists, which is a common data structure used in graph algorithms, and falls under "Algorithms" (cs.AL).
